#2. Skin preparation and drapings were done in the usual manner.
#3. 5 trocar skin incisions were made and videoscope was inserted through the subumbilical port.
#4. After thorough examination of internal organs, the greater omentum was divided close to the transverse colon.
#5. Right gastroepiploic a. and right gastric a. were divided and ligated.
#6. Endo-GIA 60 was applied on duodenum just distal to pylorus, and the duodenum was divided.
#7. The stomach was retracted upward and regional L/N dissection was done around the celiac axis and portal triad.
#8. Left gastroepiploic a. and left gastric a. were divided and ligated.
#9. Lesser omentum was retracted as close to the lesser curvature up to the cardioesophageal junction.
#10. Minilaparotomy was made on epigastrium and stomach was pulled out through it.
#11. Lesser omentum was divided as close to lesser curvature up to cardioesophageal junction.
#12. Stomach was clamped with GIA 60 and two Kelly clamps at the point of proximal one-third Then it was divided between clmps.
#13. Allen clamp from greater curvature side was applied.
#14. A loop of jejunum was brought up to the stoma of the greater curvature side and routine retrocolic gastrojejunostomy was performed.
#15. L-tube was inserted into the afferent loop
#16. A J-P drain was inserted.
#17. After warm saline irrigation and meticulous hemostasis, the operative wound was closed layer by layer.
#19. Aseptic occlusive dressing was applied on it.', '초기적재');
