#2. Skin preparation and drapings were done in the usual manner.
#3. 5 trocar skin incisions were made and videoscope was inserted through the subumbilical port.
#4. After thorough examination of internal organs, the greater omentum was divided close to the transverse colon.
#5. Right gastroepiploic a. was divided and ligated. But right gastric a. was saved.
#6. The stomach was retracted upward and regional L/N dissection was done around the celiac axis and portal triad.
#7. Left gastroepiploic a. and left gastric a. were divided and ligated.
#8. Lesser omentum was retracted as close to the lesser curvature up to the cardioesophageal junction.
#9. Minilaparotomy was made on epigastrium and stomach was pulled out through it.
- Distal margin이 pylorus에서 가까울 것으로 예상되어 Billroth-I 하기로 결정함.
#10. RGA, infrapyloric a. ligation was done.
#11. Purse-string clamp & Kelly clamp were applied on duodenum just distal to the pylorus, and the duodenum was divided between the clamps.
#12. The duodenal opening was closed with purse-string suture with Anvil in.
#13. The stomach was clamped with GIA 60 clamp from the greater curvature side at right angle around at the point of proximal one-third, then it was divided.
#14. An incision was made at ant. wall of stomach to be resected and an EEA shaft was inserted through it.
#15. The distal part of resected duodenum was brought to the stoma of the greater curvature side and gastroduodenostomy was performed with EEA 28 by tornado method.
#16. A GIA 100 was applied to the lesser curvature side and then en bloc removal was done.
#17. The lesser curvature side of remained stomach was reinforced with interrupt 3-0 CR suture.
#18. A J-P drain was inserted at rt. side.
#19. After warm saline irrigation and meticulous hemostasis, the operative wound was closed layer by layer.
#20. Aseptic occlusive dressing was applied on it.', '초기적재');
