#. Skin preparation and drapings were done in the usual manner.

#. 5 hole was made and deepened to the peritoneal cavity.
#. After thorough examination of internal organs, partial omentectomy was done.

#. Left gastroepiploic a. & Rt. gastroepiploic a. were divided and ligated.
#. The stomach was retracted upward and regional L/N dissection was done around the celiac axis and portal triad.
#. Rt. gastric a. and left gastric a. were divided and ligated.
#. Lesser omentum was retracted as close to the lesser curvature up to the cardioesophageal junction.

#. Transverse miniaparotomy was made and then stomach was pulled out.
#. Duodenal transection after purse-string clamp apply
#. Stomach transection with GIA 60 from the GC side at right angle around at the point of proximal one-third, then it was divided
#. Incision was made at AW of stomach to be resected and an EEA shaft was inserted through it
#. The distal part of resected duodenum was brought to the stomach of the greater curvature side and gastroduodenostomy was performed with EEA 28 by tornado method
#. A GIA 100 was applied to the lesser curvature side and then en bloc removal was done
#. LC side of remained stomach was reinforced with interrupt 3-0 CR suture

#. L-tube was inserted close to the anastomosis site.
#. JP drain was inserted at Rt. side to PW of stomach
#. After I&H, the operative wound was closed layer by layer.
', '초기적재');
