#. skin prep and drape
#. Subumbilical 12mm trocar was inserted with open method
#. Other trocars were inserted : 5 hole
- Lt. paraumbilicus : 12mm
- Lt. subcostal : 5mm
- Rt. paraumbilicus : 12mm
- Rt. subcostal : 5mm
#. Peritoneal exploration :
- A/A/S/S (-/-/-/-)
- Solid organ abnormality : none
#. partial omentectomy
#. Stomach mobilization and LN dissection
- GC clearing
- Lt. GEA,V ligation
#. LN dissection and LC clearing
- Rt. and Lt. gastric a. and v. ligation
- D1+ LN dissection was done
- Truncal vagotomy was done.

#. duodenal transection with endoGIA60
#. Stomach division with endoGIA60AMT * 2

#. extension of incision of umbilical port
- stomach dragged out
(Billroth I reconstruction try)
#. Hole was made at the tip of stomach and duodunum staple line
#. gastroduodenostomy was performed with endoGIA 60 purple
#. Conversion to Billroth II reconstruction d/t stenotic gastroduodenostomy
#. A loop of jejunum was brought up to the greater curvature side and antecolic gastrojejunostomy was performed
- Entry holes were made at suture line of stomach GC side and jejunum
- EndoGIA60AMT insertion via each entry hole and fired
- Common hole closure with V-lock suture
#. mesentery defect suture +
#. Hemostasis & irrigation
#. Greenplast applied
#. JP insertion : Rt.flank ~ FOW ~ to G-J anastomosis
#. Wound closure : layer by layer
