2. Skin preparation and drapings were done in the usual manner.
3. A midline skin incision was made and deepened to the peritoneal cavity.
- Rt. paramedian wound, cholecystectomy site 주변adhesion 심함.
- duodenum 주변 adhesion 심하여 BII 하기로 결정함.
4. After thorough examination of internal organs, greater omentum was divided close to the transverse colon.
5.Right gastroepiploic artery and right gastric artery were divided and ligated.
6.GIA stapler were applied on duodenum just distal to pylorus, and the duodenum was divided
7.Stomach was retracted upward and regional L/N dissection was done around the celiac axis.
8.Left gastroepiploic artery and left gastric artery were divided and ligated. Lesser omentum was divided as close to lesser curvature up to cardioesophageal junction.
9. Stomach was clamped at the point of proximal one-third Then it was divided.
10. Allen clamp from greater curvature side was applied.
11. The lesser curvature side of remaining stomach was closed with GIA stapler
12.  A loop of jejunum was brought up to the stoma of the greater curvature side and antecolic gastrojejunostomy was performed.
13. Anchoring suture was applied between mesocolon and the stomach next to G-Jstomy.
14. Braun J-J stomy
15. L-tube was inserted into the afferent loop.
16. After warm saline irrigation and complete hemostasis, the operative wound was closed in layers.
17. Aseptic occclusive dressing was applied on it.
', '초기적재');
