#. Skin preparation and draping as usual manner
#. Subumbilical 12mm trocar was inserted with open method
#. Pneumoperitoneum
#. Other trocars were inserted : 4 hole
 - Lt. paraumbilicus : 12mm
 - Lt. subcostal : 5mm
 - Rt. paraumbilicus : 12mm
 - Rt. subcostal : 5mm
#. Peritoneal exploration :
 - A/A/S/S (-/-/-/-)
 - Solid organ abnormality : negative
#. Partial omentectomy
#. GC clearing and short gastric a. and LGEA and vein ligation
#. LC clearing up to cardioesophageal junction and LN dissection
#. Lt. gastric a. and coronary vein ligation and divided
#. esophagus division using Purse-string suture with anvil in.
#. stomach devided at upper 1/3 level with stapler
 - 3b L/N FRZ bx. : No tumor (이철)
#. miniaparotomy (LLQ port extension)
 - stomach was pulled out.
 - proximal, distal RM frozen Bx : no tumor
#. Roux-limb preperation
#. side-to-side J-J anastomosis was done with endo GIA
#. End to side post. G-J anastomosis was done with endo GIA @20cm upper from the J-J stomy site
#. EEA body insertied thru distal jejunum roux limb
#. roux en Y E-J stomy made
#. roux limb stump rsection with endo GIA
#. warm saline irrigation & meticulous hemostasis
#. JP x2 inserted as described above
 - Rt. -> ant. to hepatoduodenal lig.- post. to E-J stomy-spleen
 - Lt. -> Lt. subphrenic
#. closure by layers
#. aseptic dressings
', '초기적재');
